The '''3N170''' is an [[enhancement mode]] N-Channel [[MOSFET]] standard product designed for use as a General Purpose [[amplifier]] or switch. The part was produced previously by [[Intersil]]<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://pdf1.alldatasheet.com/datasheet-pdf/view/331276/INTERSIL/3N170.html |title=3N170 pdf, 3N170 description, 3N170 datasheets, 3N170 view : ALLDATASHEET |website=Pdf1.alldatasheet.com |date= |accessdate=2017-06-07}}</ref> and other companies. and is currently produced by [[Linear Integrated Systems|Linear Integrated Systems, Inc.]]<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.linearsystems.com/lsdata/datasheets/3N170_3N171_N-Channel_Enhancement_Mode_MOSFET.pdf |format=PDF |title=Linear systems : 3N170, 3N171 |website=Linearsystems.com |accessdate=2017-06-07}}</ref>

==Part characteristics==
Characteristics include:
* Low switching voltages
* Fast switching times
* Low drain-source resistance
* Low reverse transfer capacitance

